eNCA's Lindsay Detlinger has more details. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - As President Cyril Ramaphosa remains tight-lipped over the details of the robbery at his farm, the fallout is being felt in Namibia. Namibian President Hage Geingob has denied a diplomatic cover-up while Ramaphosa won’t say whether he asked for help to keep the crime a secret. However, a Namibian intelligence report points to alleged discussions between the two heads of state. READ: Ramaphosa Farm Theft | WATCH | Geingob denies 'Farmgate' link It says South African authorities set up a meeting at the Ariamsvlei border post, with a commissioner of the Namibian police’s special branch. The report also says that due to the envisaged fallout in South Africa, Namibian authorities were asked to handle the matter with discretion. eNCA's Lindsay Detlinger has more details in the video above.